The encounter between "standard" woman and a bit spoiled coming to the prison's brutal situation arouses empathy. Here is woman like us, ordinary, loves what every woman loves, suddenly forced to fight for her place reached by surreal prison.

The series also favored due to its many colorful characters - the tough lesbian who loves rattle provocative behavior (and there are many such provocative behavior), the serious cook with a Russian accent, crazy yoga teacher, and her former lover - a drug dealer with an intellectual look.

Although the story takes place in the prison, but much of it is about life and dynamics unique to the prison, but how adviser said Chapman? "This is not Oz." This series of women, competing with other women. You can bet that instead of cruelty and the harsh reality of Oz we get a heavy dose of feminine dealing with trouble. And everything in between.